    • Uses of Readable in com.planet_ink.coffee_mud.Items.interfaces

      Subinterfaces of Readable in com.planet_ink.coffee_mud.Items.interfaces 
      Modifier and Type Interface and Description
      interface  Ammunition
      Class for ammunition items used in weapons that require ammunition
      interface  AmmunitionWeapon
      An interface for a weapon which does not work without ammunition, or which can potentially require ammunition.
      interface  Armor
      Interface for items which are complex wearables.
      interface  Book
      A book is a readable object that can usually be written to.
      interface  CagedAnimal
      Represents a MOB being stored as an Item, such as a mob in a cage, or a baby.
      interface  ClanItem
      Clan Items are variations on normal items that behave uniquely for members of clans.
      interface  Coins
      Coins are an item that represent a single coin, or a stack of dollar bills.
      interface  Computer
      A computer is a particular type of electronics panel that holds software, and has readers who monitor the messages this panel generates, as well as use the Type command to enter data into this panel's software.
      interface  Container
      A container is an item that contains other items, including other containers.
      interface  DeadBody
      Represents a player or monster corpse, dead body, a stiff.
      interface  DeckOfCards
      An interface for a deck of playing cards, like you'd use to play Gin or Poker or something.
      interface  DoorKey
      Represents a key-like thing that opens a door, or a chest, or anything else locked.
      interface  ElecPanel
      An interface for a particular kind of container that is invisible when closed, holds particular kinds of electrical gear, and allows some level of manipulation of the items inside.
      interface  Electronics
      Electronics are items that can be turned on and off before their interesting behavior or ability is available, which requires "power" to be operated, and has some capacitance for power that keeps it running for some dramatic amount of time while it is no longer receiving new power.
      interface  FalseLimb
      A False, or Fake Limb is an item that re-provides a wear location, and the personal functionality that goes with that limb, to someone who is missing that limb due to amputation.
      interface  Food
      The food interface is for items for items that can be targeted with the EAT command, and which provide nourishment that reduces hunger.
      interface  FuelConsumer
      An interface for an Electrical item that also consumes some other sort of fuel other than electrical power, if it consumes any electricity at all.
      interface  HandOfCards
      A hand of cards is a partial group of cards container, containing individual cards.
      interface  InnKey
      An InnKey is a door key that can fly back into the inventory of its shopkeeper when its time is up.
      interface  Item
      The interface for all common items, and as a base for RawMaterial, armor, weapons, etc.
      interface  Light
      A Light is an item that can emit light for some period of time.
      interface  MagicDust
      Magic Dust is itemized magic, like a potion or pill, except that it can be targeted at someone else, making malicious magic.
      interface  MiscMagic
      A MiscMagic item are magical items like Pills, Potions, Wands, Rings, Scrolls, Dust and so forth.
      interface  MusicalInstrument
      Musical instruments are typically used by Bard types to make their magic.
      interface  PackagedItems
      An interface for a large number of Items packaged into a single Item object.
      interface  Pill
      A pill is a item that bestows some magic when eaten.
      interface  PlayingCard
      A playing card is just what it sounds like - a card you can play card games with.
      interface  Potion
      A potion is an item that bestows some magic upong the drinker.
      interface  PowerGenerator
      An interface that combines both a PowerSource and and FuelConsumer to produce a Power Generator, or converter from fuel to electricity.
      interface  PowerSource
      An interface for an Electrical item that produces rather than consumes power, though it may consume something else to generate that power.
      interface  RawMaterial
      RawMaterial houses the complete list of raw resource types, which are used to specify Item materials, and the nature of raw resources.
      interface  Recipe
      A Recipe is a special readable item that, merely by having, adds to the recipes available to construction-type common skills, such as tailoring, weaponsmithing, etc.
      interface  RoomMap
      An item that, when read, shows you a graphical map of an area.
      interface  SailingShip
      A Sailing Ship, which is an object that's boardable, rooms are attached to it so you can get in, and its an item that can appear in rooms, have speed and direction, be in combat, etc.
      interface  Scroll
      A scroll is a piece of paper upon which magical spells are written.
      interface  Shield
      A shield is a large flat item useful for blocking melee attacks.
      interface  ShipEngine
      A ShipEngine is a special TechComponent that is often a fuel consumer, and which has special tracked attributes related to its ability to propel a ship and, usually, consume fuel.
      interface  ShipWarComponent
      A ship war component can be a gun or a shield generator.
      interface  Software
      Software is a plain technical item that monitors and manipulates other space ship components and systems, while also managing a user interface for players/mobs monitoring the software.
      interface  SpellHolder
      A spell holder is an item that can contain spells for use in some way, such as a scroll, staff, wand, pills, potions, etc.
      interface  TechComponent
      A TechComponent is a type of electronics item that must be installed into a panel that can accept it.
      interface  Technical
      This is the base class for all tech items.
      interface  Wand
      A wand is an item containing a magic spell that can be invoked on a target, by holding the wand, and then saying the magic word to the target.
      interface  Weapon
      An item that can be used to do damage to another mob.
